 "rat", "devops", "threat", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "note", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "note--a5a70a9d-9bb9-59e2-a836-9f1736079c77", "created": "2026-05-10T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-10T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "content": "## Summary\n**FR:** Un implant Linux sans fichier con\u00e7u pour la discr\u00e9tion et la persistance, utilisant des rootkits eBPF et des backdoors PAM pour voler des cl\u00e9s SSH et des secrets cloud.\n\n**EN:** A fileless Linux implant designed for stealth and persistence, using eBPF rootkits and PAM backdoors to steal SSH keys and cloud secrets.\n\n## Actor / Campaign / Malware / TTPs / Tools\n- Threat actor: Quasar Linux Group\n- Intrusion set: (unknown)\n- Campaign: (unknown)\n- Malware: (none)\n- MITRE TTPs: T1059.004, T1014, T1134\n- Tools: eBPF rootkit, PAM backdoor, QLNX\n\n## Analysis\n**FR:** QLNX est un malware hautement sophistiqu\u00e9 ciblant les infrastructures Linux, sp\u00e9cifiquement au sein des pipelines DevOps, pour obtenir un acc\u00e8s persistant et exfiltrer des identifiants.\n\n**EN:** QLNX is a highly sophisticated malware targeting Linux infrastructures, specifically within DevOps pipelines, to gain persistent access and exfiltrate credentials.\n\n## Recommendations\n- **[FR]:** Surveiller les programmes eBPF pour les injections non autoris\u00e9es.\n\n  **[EN]:** Monitor eBPF programs for unauthorized injections.\n- **[FR]:** Auditer le PAM (Pluggable Authentication Modules) pour les modifications inattendues.\n\n  **[EN]:** Audit PAM (Pluggable Authentication Modules) for unexpected modifications.\n\n## Indicators (defanged)\n- URLs: (none)\n- Domains: (none)\n- IPv4: (none)\n- IPv6: (none)\n- Emails: (none)\n- Hashes: (none)\n\n## Infrastructure\n(none)\n\n## Tags\nmalware, linux, rat, devops\n\n## Sources\n- https://securityaffairs.com/191898/malware/quasar-linux-rat-qlnx-a-fileless-linux-implant-built-for-stealth-and-persistence.html\n", "object_refs": ["threat-actor--1fc0cc9a-68cf-5c96-b5e1-4fee3f1db48e", "tool--33176c2e-2d59-5550-9536-d0396c87db1b", "tool--ecbac960-f6de-5c43-9a20-290fe6b33e66", "tool--ba9a8d42-705c-5ecc-8394-a6569f9457f5", "attack-pattern--8d2416a7-4366-5029-a946-bc633b765741", "attack-pattern--3f99b747-d620-570f-aede-6c92127069e3", "attack-pattern--16c72e14-c98b-57db-bafb-17a865057f39"], "abstract": "Threat | Quasar Linux RAT (QLNX) ciblant les environnements DevOps (2026-05-10)", "external_references": [{"source_name": "source", "url": "https://securityaffairs.com/191898/malware/quasar-linux-rat-qlnx-a-fileless-linux-implant-built-for-stealth-and-persistence.html"}], "labels": ["malware", "linux", "rat", "devops", "threat", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--a4cd11a6-a9a7-5e5a-87ec-fe6090b85d3d", "created": "2026-05-10T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-10T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "related-to", "source_ref": "note--a5a70a9d-9bb9-59e2-a836-9f1736079c77", "target_ref": "threat-actor--1fc0cc9a-68cf-5c96-b5e1-4fee3f1db48e", "description": "Threat note linked to referenced object", "labels": ["malware", "linux", "rat", "devops", "threat", "note-link", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--40594854-5c58-594c-be35-2e1c12b2dc52", "created": "2026-05-10T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-10T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac